{\*\cs33\b\super a}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{a}{- Mat 13.55; Mrk 6.3; Act 15.13; Gal 1.19.}}
{ From James, a servant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ:}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{Greetings to all God's people scattered over the whole world.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Faith and Wisdom}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 2}
{\*\cs33\b\super b}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{b}{- }}
{ My friends, consider yourselves fortunate when all kinds of trials come your way, }
{\*\cs4\super 3}
{for you know that when your faith succeeds in facing such trials, the result is the ability to endure. }
{\*\cs4\super 4}
{Make sure that your endurance carries you all the way without failing, so that you may be perfect and complete, lacking nothing. }
{\*\cs4\super 5}
{\*\cs33\b\super c}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{c}{- }}
{ But if any of you lack wisdom, you should pray to God, who will give it to you; because God gives generously and graciously to all. }
{\*\cs4\super 6}
{But when you pray, you must believe and not doubt at all. Whoever doubts is like a wave in the sea that is driven and blown about by the wind. }
{\*\cs4\super 7-8}
{If you are like that, unable to make up your mind and undecided in all you do, you must not think that you will receive anything from the Lord.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Poverty and Riches}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 9}
{Those Christians who are poor must be glad when God lifts them up, }
{\*\cs4\super 10}
{\*\cs33\b\super d}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{d}{- Isa 40.6,7 (LXX).}}
{ and the rich Christians must be glad when God brings them down. For the rich will pass away like the flower of a wild plant. }
{\*\cs4\super 11}
{The sun rises with its blazing heat and burns the plant; its flower falls off, and its beauty is destroyed. In the same way the rich will be destroyed while they go about their business.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Testing and Tempting}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 12}
{Happy are those who remain faithful under trials, because when they succeed in passing such a test, they will receive as their reward the life which God has promised to those who love him. }
{\*\cs4\super 13}
{\*\cs33\b\super e}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{e}{- }}
{ If we are tempted by such trials, we must not say, \uc0\u8220 This temptation comes from God.\uc0\u8221  For God cannot be tempted by evil, and he himself tempts no one. }
{\*\cs4\super 14}
{But we are tempted when we are drawn away and trapped by our own evil desires. }
{\*\cs4\super 15}
{Then our evil desires conceive and give birth to sin; and sin, when it is full-grown, gives birth to death.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 16}
{Do not be deceived, my dear friends! }
{\*\cs4\super 17}
{Every good gift and every perfect present comes from heaven; it comes down from God, the Creator of the heavenly lights, who does not change or cause darkness by turning. }
{\*\cs4\super 18}
{By his own will he brought us into being through the word of truth, so that we should have first place among all his creatures.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Hearing and Doing}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 19}
{\*\cs33\b\super f}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{f}{- }}
{ Remember this, my dear friends! Everyone must be quick to listen, but slow to speak and slow to become angry. }
{\*\cs4\super 20}
{Human anger does not achieve God's righteous purpose. }
{\*\cs4\super 21}
{So get rid of every filthy habit and all wicked conduct. Submit to God and accept the word that he plants in your hearts, which is able to save you.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 22}
{Do not deceive yourselves by just listening to his word; instead, put it into practice. }
{\*\cs4\super 23}
{If you listen to the word, but do not put it into practice you are like people who look in a mirror and see themselves as they are. }
{\*\cs4\super 24}
{They take a good look at themselves and then go away and at once forget what they look like. }
{\*\cs4\super 25}
{But if you look closely into the perfect law that sets people free, and keep on paying attention to it and do not simply listen and then forget it, but put it into practice\uc0\u8212 you will be blessed by God in what you do.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 26}
{Do any of you think you are religious? If you do not control your tongue, your religion is worthless and you deceive yourself. }
{\*\cs4\super 27}
{What God the Father considers to be pure and genuine religion is this: to take care of orphans and widows in their suffering and to keep oneself from being corrupted by the world.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Warning against Prejudice}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs2 2}
{\*\cs4\super 1}
{My friends, as believers in our Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory, you must never treat people in different ways according to their outward appearance. }
{\*\cs4\super 2}
{Suppose a rich man wearing a gold ring and fine clothes comes to your meeting, and a poor man in ragged clothes also comes. }
{\*\cs4\super 3}
{If you show more respect to the well-dressed man and say to him, \uc0\u8220 Have this best seat here,\uc0\u8221  but say to the poor man, \uc0\u8220 Stand over there, or sit here on the floor by my feet,\uc0\u8221  }
{\*\cs4\super 4}
{then you are guilty of creating distinctions among yourselves and of making judgments based on evil motives.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 5}
{Listen, my dear friends! God chose the poor people of this world to be rich in faith and to possess the kingdom which he promised to those who love him. }
{\*\cs4\super 6}
{But you dishonor the poor! Who are the ones who oppress you and drag you before the judges? The rich! }
{\*\cs4\super 7}
{They are the ones who speak evil of that good name which has been given to you.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 8}
{\*\cs33\b\super g}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{g}{- Lev 19.18.}}
{ You will be doing the right thing if you obey the law of the Kingdom, which is found in the scripture, \uc0\u8220 Love your neighbor as you love yourself.\uc0\u8221  }
{\*\cs4\super 9}
{But if you treat people according to their outward appearance, you are guilty of sin, and the Law condemns you as a lawbreaker. }
{\*\cs4\super 10}
{Whoever breaks one commandment is guilty of breaking them all. }
{\*\cs4\super 11}
{\*\cs33\b\super h}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{h}{- a Exo 20.14; Deu 5.18; b Exo 20.13; Deu 5.17.}}
{ For the same one who said, \uc0\u8220 Do not commit adultery,\uc0\u8221  also said, \uc0\u8220 Do not commit murder.\uc0\u8221  Even if you do not commit adultery, you have become a lawbreaker if you commit murder. }
{\*\cs4\super 12}
{Speak and act as people who will be judged by the law that sets us free. }
{\*\cs4\super 13}
{For God will not show mercy when he judges the person who has not been merciful; but mercy triumphs over judgment.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Faith and Actions}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 14}
{My friends, what good is it for one of you to say that you have faith if your actions do not prove it? Can that faith save you? }
{\*\cs4\super 15}
{Suppose there are brothers or sisters who need clothes and don't have enough to eat. }
{\*\cs4\super 16}
{What good is there in your saying to them, \uc0\u8220 God bless you! Keep warm and eat well!\uc0\u8221 \uc0\u8212 if you don't give them the necessities of life? }
{\*\cs4\super 17}
{So it is with faith: if it is alone and includes no actions, then it is dead.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 18}
{But someone will say, \uc0\u8220 One person has faith, another has actions.\uc0\u8221  My answer is, \uc0\u8220 Show me how anyone can have faith without actions. I will show you my faith by my actions.\uc0\u8221  }
{\*\cs4\super 19}
{Do you believe that there is only one God? Good! The demons also believe\uc0\u8212 and tremble with fear. }
{\*\cs4\super 20}
{You fool! Do you want to be shown that faith without actions is useless? }
{\*\cs33\b\super i}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{i}{a }{\*\cs51\b useless; }{some manuscripts have }{\*\cs51\b dead.}}
{ }
{\*\cs4\super 21}
{\*\cs33\b\super j}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{j}{- Gen 22.1-14 }}
{ How was our ancestor Abraham put right with God? It was through his actions, when he offered his son Isaac on the altar. }
{\*\cs4\super 22}
{Can't you see? His faith and his actions worked together; his faith was made perfect through his actions. }
{\*\cs4\super 23}
{\*\cs33\b\super k}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{k}{- a Gen 15.6; b 2Ch 20.7; Isa 41.8.}}
{ And the scripture came true that said, \uc0\u8220 Abraham believed God, and because of his faith God accepted him as righteous.\uc0\u8221  And so Abraham was called God's friend. }
{\*\cs4\super 24}
{You see, then, that it is by our actions that we are put right with God, and not by our faith alone.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 25}
{\*\cs33\b\super l}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{l}{- Jas 2.1-21.}}
{ It was the same with the prostitute Rahab. She was put right with God through her actions, by welcoming the Israelite spies and helping them to escape by a different road.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 26}
{So then, as the body without the spirit is dead, also faith without actions is dead.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{The Tongue}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs2 3}
{\*\cs4\super 1}
{My friends, not many of you should become teachers. As you know, we teachers will be judged with greater strictness than others. }
{\*\cs4\super 2}
{\*\cs33\b\super m}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{m}{- }}
{ All of us often make mistakes. But if a person never makes a mistake in what he says, he is perfect and is also able to control his whole being. }
{\*\cs4\super 3}
{We put a bit into the mouth of a horse to make it obey us, and we are able to make it go where we want. }
{\*\cs4\super 4}
{Or think of a ship: big as it is and driven by such strong winds, it can be steered by a very small rudder, and it goes wherever the pilot wants it to go. }
{\*\cs4\super 5}
{So it is with the tongue: small as it is, it can boast about great things.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{Just think how large a forest can be set on fire by a tiny flame! }
{\*\cs4\super 6}
{\*\cs33\b\super n}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{n}{- }}
{ And the tongue is like a fire. It is a world of wrong, occupying its place in our bodies and spreading evil through our whole being. It sets on fire the entire course of our existence with the fire that comes to it from hell itself. }
{\*\cs4\super 7}
{We humans are able to tame and have tamed all other creatures\uc0\u8212 wild animals and birds, reptiles and fish. }
{\*\cs4\super 8}
{But no one has ever been able to tame the tongue. It is evil and uncontrollable, full of deadly poison. }
{\*\cs4\super 9}
{\*\cs33\b\super o}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{o}{- Gen 1.26.}}
{ We use it to give thanks to our Lord and Father and also to curse other people, who are created in the likeness of God. }
{\*\cs4\super 10}
{Words of thanksgiving and cursing pour out from the same mouth. My friends, this should not happen! }
{\*\cs4\super 11}
{No spring of water pours out sweet water and bitter water from the same opening. }
{\*\cs4\super 12}
{A fig tree, my friends, cannot bear olives; a grapevine cannot bear figs, nor can a salty spring produce sweet water.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{The Wisdom from Above}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 13}
{\*\cs33\b\super p}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{p}{- }}
{ Are there any of you who are wise and understanding? You are to prove it by your good life, by your good deeds performed with humility and wisdom. }
{\*\cs4\super 14}
{But if in your heart you are jealous, bitter, and selfish, don't sin against the truth by boasting of your wisdom. }
{\*\cs4\super 15}
{Such wisdom does not come down from heaven; it belongs to the world, it is unspiritual and demonic. }
{\*\cs4\super 16}
{Where there is jealousy and selfishness, there is also disorder and every kind of evil. }
{\*\cs4\super 17}
{But the wisdom from above is pure first of all; it is also peaceful, gentle, and friendly; it is full of compassion and produces a harvest of good deeds; it is free from prejudice and hypocrisy. }
{\*\cs4\super 18}
{And goodness is the harvest that is produced from the seeds the peacemakers plant in peace.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Friendship with the World}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs2 4}
{\*\cs4\super 1}
{Where do all the fights and quarrels among you come from? They come from your desires for pleasure, which are constantly fighting within you. }
{\*\cs4\super 2}
{You want things, but you cannot have them, so you are ready to kill; you strongly desire things, but you cannot get them, so you quarrel and fight. You do not have what you want because you do not ask God for it. }
{\*\cs4\super 3}
{And when you ask, you do not receive it, because your motives are bad; you ask for things to use for your own pleasures. }
{\*\cs4\super 4}
{Unfaithful people! Don't you know that to be the world's friend means to be God's enemy? If you want to be the world's friend, you make yourself God's enemy. }
{\*\cs4\super 5}
{Don't think that there is no truth in the scripture that says, \uc0\u8220 The spirit that God placed in us is filled with fierce desires.\uc0\u8221  }
{\*\cs33\b\super q}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{q}{b }{\*\cs51\b The spirit...fierce desires; }{or }{\*\cs51\b God yearns jealously over the spirit that he placed in us.}}
{ }
{\*\cs4\super 6}
{\*\cs33\b\super r}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{r}{- Pro 3.34 (LXX).}}
{ But the grace that God gives is even stronger. As the scripture says, \uc0\u8220 God resists the proud, but gives grace to the humble.\uc0\u8221 }
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 7}
{So then, submit yourselves to God. Resist the Devil, and he will run away from you. }
{\*\cs4\super 8}
{Come near to God, and he will come near to you. Wash your hands, you sinners! Purify your hearts, you hypocrites! }
{\*\cs4\super 9}
{Be sorrowful, cry, and weep; change your laughter into crying, your joy into gloom! }
{\*\cs4\super 10}
{Humble yourselves before the Lord, and he will lift you up.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Warning against Judging One Another}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 11}
{Do not criticize one another, my friends. If you criticize or judge another Christian, you criticize and judge the Law. If you judge the Law, then you are no longer one who obeys the Law, but one who judges it. }
{\*\cs4\super 12}
{God is the only lawgiver and judge. He alone can save and destroy. Who do you think you are, to judge someone else?}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Warning against Boasting}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 13}
{\*\cs33\b\super s}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{s}{- Pro 27.1.}}
{ }
{\*\cs33\b\super t}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{t}{- }}
{ Now listen to me, you that say, \uc0\u8220 Today or tomorrow we will travel to a certain city, where we will stay a year and go into business and make a lot of money.\uc0\u8221  }
{\*\cs4\super 14}
{You don't even know what your life tomorrow will be! You are like a puff of smoke, which appears for a moment and then disappears. }
{\*\cs4\super 15}
{What you should say is this: \uc0\u8220 If the Lord is willing, we will live and do this or that.\uc0\u8221  }
{\*\cs4\super 16}
{But now you are proud, and you boast; all such boasting is wrong.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 17}
{So then, if we do not do the good we know we should do, we are guilty of sin.}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Warning to the Rich}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs2 5}
{\*\cs4\super 1}
{And now, you rich people, listen to me! Weep and wail over the miseries that are coming upon you! }
{\*\cs4\super 2}
{\*\cs33\b\super u}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{u}{- Mat 6.19.}}
{ Your riches have rotted away, and your clothes have been eaten by moths. }
{\*\cs4\super 3}
{\*\cs33\b\super v}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{v}{- }}
{ Your gold and silver are covered with rust, and this rust will be a witness against you and will eat up your flesh like fire. You have piled up riches in these last days. }
{\*\cs4\super 4}
{\*\cs33\b\super w}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{w}{- Deu 24.14,15.}}
{ You have not paid any wages to those who work in your fields. Listen to their complaints! The cries of those who gather in your crops have reached the ears of God, the Lord Almighty. }
{\*\cs4\super 5}
{Your life here on earth has been full of luxury and pleasure. You have made yourselves fat for the day of slaughter. }
{\*\cs4\super 6}
{\*\cs33\b\super x}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{x}{- }}
{ You have condemned and murdered innocent people, and they do not resist you. }
{\*\cs33\b\super y}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{y}{c }{\*\cs51\b people, and they do not resist you; }{or }{\*\cs51\b people. Will God not resist you?}}
\par\pard\plain\s5\qc\sb160\sa80\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs18\b{Patience and Prayer}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 7}
{Be patient, then, my friends, until the Lord comes. See how patient farmers are as they wait for their land to produce precious crops. They wait patiently for the autumn and spring rains. }
{\*\cs4\super 8}
{You also must be patient. Keep your hopes high, for the day of the Lord's coming is near.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 9}
{Do not complain against one another, my friends, so that God will not judge you. The Judge is near, ready to appear. }
{\*\cs4\super 10}
{My friends, remember the prophets who spoke in the name of the Lord. Take them as examples of patient endurance under suffering. }
{\*\cs4\super 11}
{\*\cs33\b\super z}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{z}{- a Job 1.21,22; 2.10; b Psa 103.8.}}
{ We call them happy because they endured. You have heard of Job's patience, and you know how the Lord provided for him in the end. For the Lord is full of mercy and compassion.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 12}
{\*\cs33\b\super a}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{a}{- Mat 5.34-37.}}
{ Above all, my friends, do not use an oath when you make a promise. Do not swear by heaven or by earth or by anything else. Say only \uc0\u8220 Yes\uc0\u8221  when you mean yes, and \uc0\u8220 No\uc0\u8221  when you mean no, and then you will not come under God's judgment.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 13}
{Are any among you in trouble? They should pray. Are any among you happy? They should sing praises. }
{\*\cs4\super 14}
{\*\cs33\b\super b}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{b}{- Mrk 6.13.}}
{ Are any among you sick? They should send for the church elders, who will pray for them and rub olive oil on them in the name of the Lord. }
{\*\cs4\super 15}
{This prayer made in faith will heal the sick; the Lord will restore them to health, and the sins they have committed will be forgiven. }
{\*\cs4\super 16}
{\*\cs33\b\super c}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{c}{- }}
{ So then, confess your sins to one another and pray for one another, so that you will be healed. The prayer of a good person has a powerful effect. }
{\*\cs4\super 17}
{\*\cs33\b\super d}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{d}{- 1Ki 17.1; 18.1 }}
{ Elijah was the same kind of person as we are. He prayed earnestly that there would be no rain, and no rain fell on the land for three and a half years. }
{\*\cs4\super 18}
{\*\cs33\b\super e}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{e}{- 1Ki 18.42-45.}}
{ Once again he prayed, and the sky poured out its rain and the earth produced its crops.}
\par\pard\plain\s7\fi240\sl-240\slmult0\f4\fs20{\*\cs4\super 19}
{My friends, if any of you wander away from the truth and another one brings you back again, }
{\*\cs4\super 20}
{\*\cs33\b\super f}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{f}{- Pro 10.12;  1Pe 4.8.}}
{ remember this: whoever turns a sinner back from the wrong way will save that sinner's soul }
{\*\cs33\b\super g}
{\footnote \pard\plain \s34\fi240\sl200\f4\fs16{g}{d }{\*\cs51\b that sinner's soul; }{or }{\*\cs51\b his own soul.}}
{ from death and bring about the forgiveness of many sins.}
